snippet.title: Geodatabase Talk
snippet.description:
The Geodatabase is a technology developed by Esri that abstracts the underlying storage medium into another layer. By doing that, you get interesting functionalities like domains, feature classes, tables, feature datasets across multiple databases from file based to enterprise RDBMS like Oracle, PostgreSQL, SQLServer DB2 etc.   

I started this podcast as a freestyle talk show where I talk about the ArcGIS geodatabase model. 

You can either head to my anchor and subscribe using your favorite podcast player https://anchor.fm/hnasr

snippet.title: Multi-User Geodatabase
snippet.description:
IGeometry is a Youtube channel that I post educational GIS videos regularly. Three weeks ago, I started this new series which I called Multi-User Geodatabase (AKA Esri SDE Geodatabase or Enterprise Geodatabase).

I always wanted to start recording episodes on Enterprise Geodatabase, after all this is what get used in real production shops! I want to explain the challenges, the complexity and the various applications that you can build on top of these geodatabases.

I record 1 episode per week (Sunday's usually). We are explaining different kind of modes in the geodatabase (Non-Versioned Without Archiving/ Non-Versioned Archiving/ Versioned without archiving and Versioned With Archiving and the difference between each one and how they actually work!)

We tackle, as always, a real-life example of implementation of the multi-user geodatabase. We take a problem and solve it using Esri's Enterprise Geodatabase as the back-end. And we also write ArcObjects code that hit this geodatabase and discuss the best practices. Throw any questions you would like answered in this series

Hope you guys enjoy it.

-Hussein Nasser

snippet.title: ArcObjects by Example C#
snippet.description:
Want to learn ArcObjects? You came to the right place, 

Ride with me as we fix a broken telecom company called "Phonetic" (terrible name I know), they suffer from losing customers, and weak phone reception despite their effort of adding new cell phone towers.. 

We are going to help them use ArcGIS to efficiently place Towers to achieve maximum reception, plus we want to do cool other things!
